  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Paraplanner",
  "description": "<p>PromiseLand Financial Advisory Pte Ltd is looking for a dedicated and reliable Paraplanner to support our Financial Advisory practice.<br />\nThis role focuses on administrative support and pre- and post-sales servicing, ensuring a smooth and professional experience for our clients, while providing some flexibility for personal sales to supplement your income.</p><h2>Key Responsibilities</h2><p>- Provide administrative support to the Financial Adviser\nRepresentative</p><p>- Handle pre-sales and post-sales documentation and\nprocessing</p><p>- Assist with policy servicing, submissions, follow-ups, and\nclient servicing matters</p><p>- Liaise with insurers and relevant parties when required</p><p>- Maintain accurate records and client documentation</p><h2>Qualifications & Licensing</h2><p>- Possess the relevant qualifications required to practise in the life and general insurance industry (e.g. M5, M8, M8A, M9, M9A, HI, BCP, PGI, ComGI, etc.)</p><p>- Minimum “O” Levels</p><p>- Diploma or Degree in Financial Planning will be an advantage</p><h2>Experience</h2><p>- Prior experience is not mandatory</p><p>- 2–3 years of experience in the Financial Services Industry\nwill be preferred</p><h2>Other Requirements</h2><p>- Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)\nand Google Workspace</p><p>- Knowledge or use of AI tools is a plus</p><p>- Able to work independently and also collaborate within a team</p><p>- Willingness to learn and grow in the financial advisory industry</p><p>- Strong sense of responsibility, integrity, and positive work ethic</p><h2>Remuneration</h2><p>- Base salary + commission structure</p><p>- Starting base salary from S$2,000 per month</p><p>- Remuneration will be commensurate with experience and\nqualifications</p>",
